Guaranteed Yield to Surrender prorates the bonus over the surrender charge period: base rate + [bonus rate (if any) / surrender charge period]. For multi-year guaranteed fixed (MYG/MYGA) annuities, it is usually the same as average annual yield. Guaranteed Yield to Surrender for traditional products assumes that once the initial term of the base rate is over, the contract renews at the Guaranteed Rate for the remaining term of surrender charge period. Since future renewal rates are unknown, actual yield to surrender over the life of the contract may be higher than the Guaranteed Yield to Surrender.
A predetermined interest rate threshold that enables the policyholder to withdraw funds without surrender charges if the renewal rate drops below this level.
